After 20 mins, these are the items I got: 12-bar MRE box,  a hatchet,  a heavy-duty 16/12in foldable grill, a cooking utensil kit, a cookware kit(a pot, pan and kettle), 2 thermoflasks(for water), a sleeping bag, a rain coat, a 14 piece survial kit( a folding knife, a pocket bellow, 3 carabiners, emergency blanket, Flint stone & scrapper, credit card knife, and a compass all in a water proof box), and a tactical military backpack. It came up to a grand sum of 11 items for $337.73. Not bad all things considered.

snippet.textDisplay: Could be fun to show an actual survival expert the items you chose, then ask them to teach you what you would actually need. For instance, instead of getting a pre-made first-aid kit, I found it to be much more cost effective to get the individual items, especially since commercial first-aid kits tend to have a lot of junk you don't really need, and not enough of the stuff you actually wind up using.
